socket++
------------------------------------------
Socket++ library defines a family of C++ classes that can be used more
effectively than directly calling the underlying low-level system functions.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.4-2
  libgcc1-11.2.0-1
  libsocket++-devel-1.12.13-1bl2
  libsocket++1-1.12.13-1bl2
  libstdc++6-11.2.0-1
  pkg-config-1.8.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.37-2
  cygport-0.34.2-1
  gcc-core-11.2.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.2.0-1
  libtool-2.4.7-1
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/hstraub/socketxx

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/hstraub/socketxx.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack socket++-1.12.13-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./socket++-1.12.13-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/socket++-1.12.13-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/socket++-1.12.13-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsocket++1-1.12.13-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsocket++-devel-1.12.13-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(socket++)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/socket++.README
  /usr/share/doc/socket++/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/socket++/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/socket++/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/socket++/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/socket++/README
  /usr/share/doc/socket++/THANKS

(libsocket++1)
  /usr/bin/cygsocket++-1.dll

(libsocket++-devel)
  /usr/include/socket++/echo.h
  /usr/include/socket++/fork.h
  /usr/include/socket++/ftp.h
  /usr/include/socket++/pipestream.h
  /usr/include/socket++/protocol.h
  /usr/include/socket++/sig.h
  /usr/include/socket++/smtp.h
  /usr/include/socket++/sockinet.h
  /usr/include/socket++/sockstream.h
  /usr/include/socket++/sockunix.h
  /usr/lib/libsocket++.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/socket++.pc

